parameters: Clea: I came to collect Frimata-san's debt.

by talking to a gambler?'

Clea: I dislike clever tricks, but I will make sure to
collect the debt, even if I have to do it forcefully.
The solitary gambler: Hmph... Fine, I'll repay Frimata.

Innkeeper: There aren't enough varieties to get lost in your
order, right?

Drunk old lady: The only good thing about Marako Village is
that an old lady like me can drink alcohol during the day.

Drunk customer: What...? If you're not going to buy me a
drink, then go somewhere else!

Innkeeper: Welcome to the Village of Despair. I am a kind
person who drowns fools in alcohol.
